descript.abstract: This map data layer represents the building footprints for the City of El Paso, Texas.The building footprints data layer was originally based on aerial photographs from 2007.
descript.purpose: As part of the basemap data layers, the building footprints map layer is an integral part of the City of El Paso Geographic Information System. Basemap data layers are accessed by personnel in most City departments for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production. More advanced user applications may focus on planning, public works, or utilities purposes (including defining boundaries, managing assets and facilities, integrating attribute databases with geographic features, spatial analysis, and presentation output).
